name: v3.1.6
body:
- fix explicit array cast for ASSIGN_DIM
- add Threaded::notifyOne
- fix bug in Threaded properties causing incorrect objects to be fetched by read
- fix bug in trait aliases
- fix INHERIT_NONE breaking lambdas
- fix bug in constant copy routine for 7.1

name: v3.1.3
body: - Fix intermittent fault caused by freeing global strings too early

name: v3.1.1
body: - Fix fault when ::shutdown (or ::join) is called before ::start

name: v3.1.0
body:
API now finalized for PHP7.
Various fixes, everyone must upgrade.

name: v3.0.8
body:
Fix gh issue #495 (AST copy bug)
Fig gh issue #493 (exception handler bug)
Improve stability with critical section in a couple of places during startup/shutdown
Remove remainder of kill junk
Be delicious ...

name: v3.0.7
body:
This release removes Thread::kill, there's no good way to do that.
It fixes many bugs found by AddressSanitizer
Upgrade immediately, please :)

name: v3.0.6
body:
This release disables pthreads in all but the CLI SAPI.

After many years of advising that multi-threading at the frontend doesn't make sense, I'm promoting the advice to hard and fast fact.

Note that pthreads can still be loaded by phpdbg, but using phpdbg and pthreads is not recommended, phpdbg is ill prepared, I hope to fix that sometime ...

name: v3.0.4
body: Fix fault caused by accessing uninitialized (std) properties table in various handlers

name: v3.0.3
body: Coercion of arrays to Volatile objects is the main change in this release, as well as a few fixes for bugs reported since last release.

name: v3.0.2
body:
fix gh issue #484 
support object comparison
do not allow exception handlers that are inconsistent with thread options to be copied

name: v3.0.0
body:
I'm excited to tag this first release of pthreads v3, which represents a giant leap forwards in efficiency for pthreads and targets PHP7 only.

A summary of changes can be found in the readme, changes are further explained in the following blog posts:
- [A Letter from the Future](http://blog.krakjoe.ninja/2015/08/a-letter-from-future.html)
- [Addendum: Letter from the Future](http://blog.krakjoe.ninja/2015/09/addendum-letter-from-future.html)

The documentation is not yet updated in the PHP manual, if you feel like volunteering to help with that, please do.
